 technician </strong></h3><p><strong>STEP 1: Obtain a European certificate</strong></p><p>Anyone who wants to work as a fire protection equipment technician in the Flemish Region and does not yet have a <strong>European certificate</strong> must <strong>take</strong> an <strong>exam</strong> at a recognised training centre. The exam consists of a theory and practical part. The content of the theory and practical examination is laid down in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=43369&amp;woLang=nl\">annex to regulation 304/2008</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://datasets.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/be.vl.omgeving.erkenningen.distribution.opleidingscentra_technici_brandbeveiligingsapparatuur.pdf\">Download the list of recognised training centres for fire protection equipment technicians here.</a></p><p>Those who pass the exam receive a <strong>European certificate</strong> (certificate of competence). The training institute also registers your certificate in the Database of Qualifications and Professional Experience Attestations (LED) of the Flemish government.</p><p><strong>STEP 2: </strong><a href=\"https://loket-erkenningen-leefmilieu.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/registreer-voor-erkenning-van-rechtswege\">Register for recognition as a fire protection equipment technician via the self-management counter 'My VLAREL recognition'</a>.</p><ul><li>You need to register with your eID at the counter. Without registration, you cannot start working as a fire protection equipment technician. </li><li>Once you have obtained a <strong>European certificate </strong>and <strong>registered </strong>, you will receive an <strong>e-mail with your recognition number</strong> and further info.</li></ul><h3><strong>You already have a European certificate as a fire protection equipment technician </strong></h3><p><strong>STEP 1: </strong><a href=\"https://loket-erkenningen-leefmilieu.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/registreer-voor-erkenning-van-rechtswege\">Register for recognition as a fir